---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const seoTitle = "About";
const seoDescription = "CasiLocal Spots is a directory strictly for finding workspaces in Madrid, distinguishing it from a general travel or food guide.";
---

<Layout title={seoTitle} description={seoDescription}>
  <main class="w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 md:py-20 space-y-16">
    
    <!-- 1. Header Area -->
    <section class="space-y-6 text-center">
      <h1 class="font-display font-black text-6xl md:text-8xl tracking-tighter leading-[0.9] text-[var(--color-ink)]">
        About
      </h1>
      <p class="font-display italic text-2xl md:text-3xl text-[var(--color-ink)] leading-tight max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        A directory strictly for finding workspaces in Madrid.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="border-b-2 border-dotted border-[var(--color-ink)]/20 w-full"></div>

    <!-- 2. Mission Statement -->
    <section class="prose prose-lg prose-headings:font-display prose-p:font-body text-[var(--color-ink)] max-w-none">
      <h2 class="font-display font-black text-3xl mb-4">The Utility of Excellence</h2>
      <p>
        CasiLocal Spots is explicitly <strong>not</strong> a standard review platform like Google Maps or Yelp. 
        We do not rate places based on "vibes" or "friendliness" alone. We rate them based on their <span class="font-bold bg-[var(--color-brass)]/30 px-1 rounded-sm">Utility for Production</span>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Can you actually get things done here? Is the wifi fast enough for a video call? 
        We believe that <strong>quality is infrastructure</strong>. A spot with burnt coffee or a wobbly table is just as broken as a spot with slow wifi. 
        We demand excellence in both the digital connection and the physical product.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- 3. Metric Legend -->
    <section class="space-y-8">
      <h2 class="font-display font-black text-3xl mb-6">The Legend</h2>
      
      <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2">
        
        <!-- WiFi -->
        <article class="space-y-3 p-6 border-2 border-[var(--color-ink)] rounded-sm bg-white shadow-card hover:shadow-card-hover transition-shadow duration-300">
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-xl border-b-2 border-dotted border-[var(--color-ink)]/20 pb-2">WiFi Speed</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-[var(--color-ink)]">
              <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-ember)]">Flynet:</strong> Fiber-optic speeds. Video calls, large uploads, zero lag.</li>
              <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-moss)]">Reliable:</strong> Solid for general work, email, and browsing.</li>
              <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-oxide)]">Spotty:</strong> Good for offline work, but risk of dropping.</li>
              <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-oxide)]">Detox:</strong> No internet. Pure focus (or panic).</li>
            </ul>
        </article>

        <!-- Noise -->
        <article class="space-y-3 p-6 border-2 border-[var(--color-ink)] rounded-sm bg-white shadow-card hover:shadow-card-hover transition-shadow duration-300">
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-xl border-b-2 border-dotted border-[var(--color-ink)]/20 pb-2">Noise Level</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-[var(--color-ink)]">
              <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-moss)]">Library:</strong> Pin-drop quiet. Strict focus.</li>
              <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-brass)]">Hum:</strong> The standard cafe buzz. White noise for productivity.</li>
              <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-oxide)]">Lively:</strong> Blenders, chatter, movement. Headphones recommended.</li>
            </ul>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2">
         <!-- Plugs -->
         <article class="space-y-3 p-6 border-2 border-[var(--color-ink)] rounded-sm bg-white shadow-card hover:shadow-card-hover transition-shadow duration-300">
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-xl border-b-2 border-dotted border-[var(--color-ink)]/20 pb-2">Plug Access</h3>
            <p>
                A simple binary check. Either outlets are accessible to users at tables, or they are not. We don't count the hidden socket behind the fridge.
            </p>
        </article>

        <!-- Casi Score -->
        <article class="space-y-3 p-6 border-2 border-[var(--color-ink)] rounded-sm bg-white shadow-card hover:shadow-card-hover transition-shadow duration-300">
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-xl border-b-2 border-dotted border-[var(--color-ink)]/20 pb-2">The "Casi" Score</h3>
            <p>
                A weighted suitability calculation strictly for work. It combines <strong>Ergonomics</strong> (comfort), 
                <strong>Connectivity</strong> (wifi/power), and <strong>Quality</strong> (coffee/service) into a single rating. 
                If any pillar fails, the score reflects it.
            </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 4. Methodology -->
    <section class="p-8 bg-[var(--color-paper)] border-2 border-[var(--color-ink)] rounded-sm relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-grain opacity-50 pointer-events-none"></div>
        <div class="relative z-10 space-y-4">
            <h2 class="font-display font-black text-3xl">Methodology</h2>
            <p class="font-body text-lg">
                Our data comes from a hybrid engine of two sources:
            </p>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-4">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-lg mb-1">Automated Analysis</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm">We synthesize thousands of public user reviews using NLP to detect specific patternsâ€”filtering for keywords like "wifi", "laptops", "sockets", and "noise".</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-lg mb-1">Manual Verification</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm">Physical spot-checks. We actually go there, order a coffee, and try to work. If the wifi fails, the data changes.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="border-b-2 border-dotted border-[var(--color-ink)]/20 w-full"></div>

    <!-- 5. Disclaimer -->
    <section class="text-[var(--color-ink)]/80 text-sm font-body max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center space-y-2">
      <h3 class="font-display font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-xs">Note on Accuracy</h3>
      <p>
        Businesses change. Modems break, outlets get covered, and quiet corners become brunch hotspots. 
        This directory is a living document. Verify before you commit to a full day of deep work.
      </p>
    </section>

  </main>
</Layout>
